Kentucky at War




In our archive we have 5,355 Gold Star casualties from Kentucky .. those who were born, raised or lived in, enlisted from, or were in some other way significantly associated with the state during four major wars of the 20th century. Here are the casualty numbers for each war: World War I - 500 World War II - 2,903 Korean War - 893 Vietnam War - 1,059In addition, we have identified 28 U.S. service members from all states who suffered casualties on 09-25-1968 .. the same day as Sergeant David Thomas Seaton.Important Note - These statistics are based on our archival data, which is about 95% complete for Korea and Vietnam, but only about 50% for WW I and II.





